==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sundry
<hw>Sun"dry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sundry</ets>, <ets>sondry</ets>, AS. <ets>syndrig</ets>, fr.
<ets>sundor</ets> asunder. See <er>Sunder</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Several; divers; more than one or two; various.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sundry</xex> wines.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sundry</xex> weighty reasons.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With many a sound of <qex>sundry</qex> melody.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sundry</qex> foes the rural realm surround.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Separate; diverse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every church almost had the Bible of a <qex>sundry</qex>
translation.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>All and sundry</b></col>, <cd>all collectively, and each
separately.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sundryman</ent>⟦br⟧
